{
  "stem": "24242.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not in '41-- earlier. '39 or '40.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, talking politics with neighbors.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Used to come, neighbors, and say to my father that he should take his family and escape, because a bad time is coming up in the state of White Russia.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I don't think most of the population believed [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] those people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of my brothers, Abraham-- he married to one of those girls that escaped from deep Poland, where it was occupied by the Nazis, I guess, in 1939.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And she was telling us stories.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then behind her back, I remember my mother, my father would not believe [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that the Nazis just random killing Jews.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were not the only ones who did not believe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Others also-- other Jewish people-- did not trust or believe those few Jews that escaped from the Nazi-occupied Poland into state of White Russia.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I hope I've made myself clear.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, they spoke about the Nazis, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Me as a child?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not too much, really, but I wouldn't-- I couldn't answer that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I couldn't answer that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the war started the 22nd of June, 1941.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And within two or three days, really, the Nazis dropped [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the-- what do you call?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The parachute people, parachute soldiers, and the Nazis were even in our village.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And this is where-- from here I can tell you, for the next few years, our problem.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When did I first see them?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I saw them, as I said, two or three days right after the war started.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nazi soldiers coming with one Gentile policeman.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
